      },
      "lineNbr": 2804,
      "author": {
        "id": 6155
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T16:20:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So this flattens a stream if you can\u0027t get the base address right away? Does that create a flattened copy?",
      "revId": "1ca3c4589ec8c41954db9037e4ea2e7a963ae7b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b855b84e_b1106794",
        "filename": "src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 2804,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T17:20:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. Unfortunately, CFData always wants flattened data. On the other hand, it turns out that internally the CoreText code was always taking the CGDataProvider and making a copy all the time anyway (to ensure it was flattened, I suppose). Now that we\u0027re passing it a CFData it appears at least one copy is skipped when the common case of the stream being backed by contiguous memory.",
      "parentUuid": "49c83da2_33f9b79b",
      "revId": "1ca3c4589ec8c41954db9037e4ea2e7a963ae7b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
