      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T20:00:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the explanations.",
      "parentUuid": "b855b84e_b1106794",
      "revId": "1ca3c4589ec8c41954db9037e4ea2e7a963ae7b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "09df9560_6215eac6",
        "filename": "src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 2810,
      "author": {
        "id": 6155
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T16:20:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can this be const?",
      "revId": "1ca3c4589ec8c41954db9037e4ea2e7a963ae7b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9f837315_4adb9198",
        "filename": "src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 2810,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T17:20:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Everything here can be const! The only reason anything has names in here is either for sequence ordering (using data before release\u0027ing it), so we can take the address of it, or so it can be disposed of automatically. It would be nice to use a language where nothing in here needed to be named.",
      "parentUuid": "09df9560_6215eac6",
      "revId": "1ca3c4589ec8c41954db9037e4ea2e7a963ae7b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "217c9761_46ff8401",
        "filename": "src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 2810,
      "author": {
        "id": 6395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T20:00:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am not sure I follow completely - could you elaborate what you mean by \"having names\"? You mean the memory blocks that we\u0027re passing to be owned by CF? I was thinking whether it could be \"const CFAllocatorContext ctx \u003d ...\".",
      "parentUuid": "9f837315_4adb9198",
      "revId": "1ca3c4589ec8c41954db9037e4ea2e7a963ae7b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "82765b40_fffccebe",
        "filename": "src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 2810,
      "author": {
        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-11-12T20:17:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It would be nice to write this like\n\nreturn CFDataCreateWithBytesNoCopy(\n    kCFAllocatorDefault,\n    data-\u003edata(),\n    data-\u003esize(),\n    CFAllocatorCreate(\n        kCFAllocatorDefault,\n        {\n            0,\n            data.release(),\n            ...\n        }\n     )\n);\n\nbut we\u0027re just prevented from doing so due to parameter evaluation ordering issues (don\u0027t want to call data.release() before data-\u003edata()) and CFAllocatorCreate taking the context by address (so we need to give it a name to take its address). Also we don\u0027t want to make this a const CFAllocatorContext because CFAllocatorCreate takes a non-const pointer to CFAllocatorContext, so we would need to cast away the const explicitly anyway, and the scope is so short here that it wouldn\u0027t add much for the reader of the code.",
      "parentUuid": "217c9761_46ff8401",
      "revId": "1ca3c4589ec8c41954db9037e4ea2e7a963ae7b2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
